@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.Contacts.UI

@*
    Help content for the Contacts module.
    Based on docs/user/CONTACTS.md.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>DotNetCloud Contacts lets you store and manage your contacts, organize them into groups, share them with other users, and sync with external applications via CardDAV.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Managing Contacts</h2>
        <p><strong>Creating a contact:</strong> Click <strong>New Contact</strong> and fill in the details: display name (required), names, organization, email addresses, phone numbers, addresses, birthday, website, and notes.</p>
        <p><strong>Editing:</strong> Click on a contact to open it, edit any fields, and click <strong>Save</strong>.</p>
        <p><strong>Deleting:</strong> Select a contact and click <strong>Delete</strong>. Contacts are soft-deleted.</p>
        <p><strong>Searching:</strong> Use the search bar to find contacts by name, email, phone number, or organization. Results update as you type.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Contact Groups</h2>
        <p><strong>Creating a group:</strong> In the Contacts sidebar, click <strong>New Group</strong> and enter a name.</p>
        <p><strong>Adding contacts:</strong> Open a contact and select the groups to add it to, or open a group and click <strong>Add Members</strong>.</p>
        <p><strong>Removing:</strong> Open a group and click the remove button next to a contact. Removing a contact from a group does not delete the contact.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Sharing Contacts</h2>
        <p>Share your contacts with other DotNetCloud users. You can control whether they can view or edit shared contacts.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">CardDAV Sync</h2>
        <p>Contacts are accessible via CardDAV, allowing sync with external applications like Thunderbird, Apple Contacts, or mobile devices. Use your DotNetCloud credentials to connect.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Use groups to organize contacts by project, team, or relationship.</li>
            <li>Add multiple email addresses and phone numbers with different labels for flexibility.</li>
            <li>Use the search bar for quick access — it searches across all contact fields.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
